@inproceedings{WOS:000082419500004,
  abstract = {Examples of vegetative variation, observed in infrageneric taxa of
Bactris, are given for the most variable and confusing groups: B.
simplicifrons complex, B. hirta complex, B. pectinata complex. B.
acanthocarpa complex and B. maraja complex. From a table giving the
number of synonyms and the size of the distribution area for each
accepted species, it appears that vegetative variation is highly related
to the taxa and to the size of their distribution area. Variation is
mostly found in leaves and indument. A comprehensive review of Bactris
should be possible by combining floral and vegetative characters with
anatomy, pollen and pollinators, ecology, germination and seedlings, and
molecular methods.},
