@article{WOS:000334359600003,
  abstract = {A compilation of the known natural history of adult Cetoniinae
(Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) from Argentina and adjacent countries is
provided. Food items of adult Cetoniinae include pollen and/or nectar
(flower visitors), sap and/ or slime flux, ripened fruits on plants,
green tissues and leaves, and honey. Of the 36 species of Cetoniinae
from Argentina, food items are known only for 11 species (30.5\%).
Attraction to light and bait- traps, adult activity periods, vertebrate
predators, and the occurrence in bird nests are presented and discussed.
Other insects that share the same food sources and bait- traps with
Cetoniinae are mentioned.},
