@article{WOS:A1983RT84700002,
  abstract = {One new species of Aristolochia, A. singalangensis, is described from
Sumatra. This is the only Malesian species to have the fruit dehiscing
from the apex towards the base. Remarks are made on the taxonomy,
nomenclature, typification, characteristics for identification,
relationship, distribution, etc. of some of Asiatic and Malesian
species, all belonging to Aristolochia except Thottea philippinensis.
The phenomena and significance of aristolochiaceous plant-butterfly
relationships are discussed. Germinated pollen grains were found in
dehisced anthers of open flowers in both Aristolochia and Thottea.
