@article{WOS:A1989AL76100008,
  abstract = {It is shown possible to evaluate the genetic similarity of the
homozygous genotypes of the self-pollinated cross by means of the
parentage coefficient. The parentage coefficients for 1596 pair
combinations of 57 varieties and lines of spring common wheat of the
Saratov breed have been computed. The cluster analysis has singled out
10 clusters with high mean intracluster parentage coefficients
(0.50-0.77). All clusters with the exception of one are in parentage at
the half-sib level (R =  0.10-0.37). A correlation is found between the
parentage coefficient and the similarity indices based on the gliadin
markers (r = 0.40), and with allowance for some morphological markers r
= 0.46. The parentage coefficient can be expediently used within the
two-component method for the planning of simple and complex crosses.},
