@inproceedings{WOS:000086521700036,
  abstract = {Wild populations of Cycas in Thailand Vietnam, and China were surveyed
for insects. Beetles in two families were found to occur consistently
and abundantly in cones of Cycas. Twenty-six undescribed species of
weevils (family Curculionidae) in the genus Tychiodes were identified
from male cones in 22 Cycas populations in Thailand and Vietnam. These
are classified into three groups, and weevils from each group may occur
together on the cones of many Cycas populations. Also, 17 species of
beetles (family Languriidae, tribe Xenoscelini) in the genus Xenocryptus
were abundant on both male and female cones in 15 Cycas populations in
Thailand Vietnam, and China. These Xenocryptus beetles are closely
related to beetles believed to pollinate cycads in Mexico, Florida, and
South Africa. We suspect that both the Tychiodes and Xenocryptus beetles
are involved in the pollination of Cycas. A preliminary phylogeny of
these beetles parallels a phylogeny of Southeast Asian Cycas produced
from a gel-electrophoretic study of Cycas proteins. Speciation in Cycas
cone beetles appears to parallel speciation in Cycas in Southeast Asia
and beetles appear to provide a useful tool for investigating Cycas
taxonomy.},
