@article{WOS:000463297500048,
  abstract = {Arum Italicum Mill. fruits that have antioxidant effect and some
phenolic compounds were investigated at its different maturation stages.
Observing of some phenolic compounds like ellagic acid, hesperidin,
resveratrol and quercetin varied from depending on their ripening stages
in harvest as immature, half mature and mature crops. These compounds
can be recovered from Arum Italicum Mill. fruits by using the Soxhlet
extraction method in methanol for four hours. And, the phenolic
compounds in these fruits can easily be identified by using HPLC-DAD
device. It is obvious that the amounts of ellagic acid, hesperidin,
resveratrol and quercetin in half-mature fruits of Arum Italicum Mill.
decrease and even hesperidin, resveratrol and quercetin disappear
altogether. While the antioxidant effect was determined by using DPPH
